{
  "info": {
    "name": "Demand-Supply Matching API (Part 3 & 4)",
    "description": "Two folders: 'Example 1' and 'Example 2', replaying both worked examples from the exercise spec through the live REST API. Order ids are auto-generated by the server (Part 4) -- each request's test script captures the returned id into a collection variable so later requests (including status lookups) can reference them without copy-pasting. Run each folder's requests top to bottom. Truncate both DB tables and restart the Spring Boot app before switching from one folder to the other, so auto-generated ids restart cleanly at 1. A third folder, 'Edit & Cancel (PUT/DELETE)', exercises the PUT (price/quantity edit) and DELETE (cancel remaining quantity) endpoints, including the 409 responses when an order is no longer in an editable/cancellable state. Request 0 at the top level (outside any folder) is a full reset -- DELETE /api/orders wipes every order and trade (DB + in-memory) and restarts auto-generated ids at 1. Run it before starting (or re-running) any folder below, instead of manually truncating tables in MySQL.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:8080"
    },
    {
      "key": "s1_id",
      "value": ""
    },
    {
      "key": "s2_id",
      "value": ""
    },
    {
      "key": "s3_id",
      "value": ""
    },
    {
      "key": "d1_id",
      "value": ""
    },
    {
      "key": "d2_id",
      "value": ""
    },
    {
      "key": "d3_id",
      "value": ""
    },
    {
      "key": "edit_s_id",
      "value": ""
    },
    {
      "key": "edit_d_id",
      "value": ""
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "0. RESET \u2014 delete ALL orders & trades (start fresh)",
      "request": {
        "method": "DELETE",
        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/orders"
      },
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('204 No Content', () => pm.response.to.have.status(204));"
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Example 1",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "1. Add supply order (tomato 24/kg 100kg) -> captures s1_id",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('s1_id', body.orderId);",
                  "pm.test('201 Created', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/orders/supply",
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"time\": \"09:45\",\n  \"produce\": \"tomato\",\n  \"price\": 24,\n  \"quantity\": 100\n}"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "2. Add supply order (tomato 20/kg 90kg) -> captures s2_id",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
